This paper is about improving the stability and performance of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) algorithms, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new algorithm that improves the learning process of DRL models. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as DRL is a subfield of AI and the paper deals with improving the performance of AI agents. The third likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as DRL is often used in robotics applications and the paper's proposed algorithm could improve the stability and performance of robotic agents. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as DRL is also used in control systems and the paper's proposed algorithm could improve the stability and performance of such systems. The fifth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as DRL is also used in computer vision applications and the paper's proposed algorithm could improve the stability and performance of vision-based agents.
